article.description: — David Roddy had 26 points and 11 rebounds as Colorado State defeated Wyoming 61-55 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Roddy scores 26 to carry Colorado St. over Wyoming 61-55
article.linkText: Roddy scores 26 to carry Colorado St. over Wyoming 61-55
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. -- — David Roddy had 26 points and 11 rebounds as Colorado State defeated Wyoming 61-55 on Wednesday night. Chandler Jacobs had 18 points and seven rebounds for Colorado State (22-4, 12-4 Mountain West Conference). Isaiah Stevens added 10 points and six assists. Drake Jeffries had 22 points and seven rebounds for the Cowboys (22-5, 11-3). Xavier DuSell added 11 points. Graham Ike had 13 rebounds. The Rams leveled the season series against the Cowboys. Wyoming defeated Colorado State 84-78 on Jan. 31. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
